The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

THE FILM

 (September 8) Directed by Oscar-winning German film-maker 

 Florian Gallenberger, Shadows of Time is the tragic 

 love story of Ravi and Masha that begins in a carpet factory, 

 and dominates the rest of their lives. The Bengali film 

 stars Tannishtha Chatterjee, Prashant Narayanan, Irrfan, 

 Soumitra Chatterjee and Sova Sen. Releases at INOX (Forum 

 and City Centre), and 89 Cinemas. 

 THE DISPLAY

 (Seagull Arts amp; Media Resource Centre, 2 pm-8 pm, till 

 September 15) The exhibition of paintings by Reba Hore is 

 a repeat of the earlier show at Seagull enriched with a 

 whole new body of her works. 

 THE LAUNCH

 (Oxford 

 Bookstore, 6.30 pm September 5) Racists, Kunal Basus 

 third novel, will be launched by Penguin. Followed by an interaction 

 between the author and British Council director Sujata Sen. 




